description: Larotrectinib is a small-molecule inhibitor of NTRK1/2/3 that is FDA-approved for the treatment of adult and pediatric patients with solid tumors that have an NTRK gene fusion without a known acquired resistance mutation. NTRK3 F617L is listed in the FDA label for larotrectinib as a resistance mutation. At least one patient with an NTRK-fusion-positive tumor acquired an NTRK3 F617L mutation upon progression on larotrectinib (PMID: 31738426, 30624546). This mutation is considered a gatekeeper residue (Abstract: Drilon et al. Abstract# 4000, AACR 2019. https://tptherapeutics.com/wp-content/uploads/AACR_2019_TRK_Final_S.pdf).
